, \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Molly_Hayes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Molly_Hayes\"}, {\"begin\": 245, \"end\": 255, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Darlington_Raceway\", \"score\": 0.9999999785659386, \"rank\": 1.5910009905320564e-08, \"text\": \"Darlington\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Darlington_Raceway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Darlington_Raceway\"}, {\"begin\": 256, \"end\": 263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"REUTERS\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 273, \"end\": 284, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"score\": 0.9999977889573871, \"rank\": 2.153243527712408e-06, \"text\": \"Philippines\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Delgaco registered her fastest time in the Olympics as she finished 20th overall in the women's single sculls after placing second in the classification final D at the Vaires-sur-Marne Nautical Stadium on Friday, August 2.\", \"from\": 378, \"to\": 600, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 546, \"end\": 562, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vaires-sur-Marne\", \"score\": 0.9999999998831299, \"rank\": 1.1691040055694604e-10, \"text\": \"Vaires-sur-Marne\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vaires-sur-Marne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vaires-sur-Marne\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Crossing the first 1,000 meters at fifth place, the pride of Iriga, Camarines Sur pulled out all the stops in the last 1,000 meters to clock 7 minutes and 43.83 seconds.\", \"from\": 602, \"to\": 771, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 663, \"end\": 668, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.o